,Recommended,225080,8571698,"Posted: 5 January, 2014",all,Meatbug,"Brilliant game!The gameplay feels great, it is emotional, touching and looks and sounds pretty nice. A small but beautiful fairy tale.You'll play as two brothers, an older and a younger one, on their quest for a cure to their sick father.Both are controlled via the analog-sticks on the controller. You can control them separately and move them around independently, which is also needed for a lot of the puzzles throughout the game, but it is not as hard as it might sound (imho).You will encounter some obstacles on your journey which you need to overcome, e.g. you are tied together with a rope and you need to climb a tower. While one brother hangs on a ledge, the other one swings to another ledge, now hanging there to let the other brother swing to the platform you need to climb.Both have also different ""abilitys"": The older brother is capable of lifting the younger one onto higher platforms, he wouldn't be able to climb otherwise, while the younger one can slip through small passages.The artstyle and visuals are very beautiful and the sound adds a lot of emotion to it.Highly recommended!"
