,Recommended,225080,8145941,"Posted: 20 December, 2013",all,TastyEmpire,"There really isn't a way for me to recommend this game enough. I played it when it came out on the 360 and had to buy it again on Steam.The first thing to know about this game is that it's ideally suited to a gampad with two analog sticks. It's possible to play with a mouse and keyboard, but it was specifically designed with a dual analog stick controller in mind.The gameplay mechanics can take a little getting used to, but after a short time, they feel very fluid and natural. You control one brother with the left stick and left trigger and the other brother with the right stick and right trigger. Those are the only buttons you use. Sounds simple and it is, but it's so unique. I've never played a game like this as far as controlling characters and it's truly a joy to play.The puzzles are fairly simple, but satisfying. The music is absolutely beautiful. The graphics aren't going to push your graphics card, but they are definitely appealing.The story is at times funny, hopeful, touching, and incredibly sad. There is no spoken language in the game, but it does an amazing job conveying emotions via the characters gestures and vocalizations.This is definitely one the most interesting games I've played in a very long time and I highly recommend that you give it a try."
