76561198062301817,Recommended,225080,32035212,Posted: 28 May,all,Rhythm Raph,"Perfect if you like games with the same vibe as Journey, Ico and the likes. Controlling each brother with a joystick may be confusing at first, but it quickly becomes a second nature. It's a refreshing game mechanic, and it leads to original and sometimes challenging puzzles.I found myself often impressed by the landscape, and would stop playing to contemplate my surroundings, a thing that I rarely do in games.I love the fact that the game conveys as little information as possible, be it the rules or the narrative. It tells you briefly the controls, and you have to figure out yourself what you can and can't do (other games can't do it as easily since they have more complicated controls, whereas in Brothers, you only have two joysticks and two buttons, but the simplicity of controls doesn't stop some games from over-explaining things to the player). The narrative is as simple as it can be, with no intelligible dialogues and a pretty straightforward quest, but it still manages to make you live memorable moments, to give a lasting impression and to have one of the most touching ending in a video game."
