,Not Recommended,225080,32475081,Posted: 16 June,all,Daniel Potter,"This is a contreversial opinion, but i don't like this game. I tried to like. I replayed it again, just to see if my opinion would change.Before you start saying that i have no heart, i have played games like walking dead, life is strange, valiant hearts. Have cried on all of them, but in this game - nothing.The game is only 2 hours long. I think in that short time, it just fails to establish a connection between the player and the characters. The characters themselves speak only in gibberish, and because of that they never really engage in lengthy conversations, mostly it's body language. Finally, i think the music is just not good enough, which is very important if you want the audience to cry.https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=i8HePfa7WYsThat said, the game has its pros, and it's the exposition. Throughout the game, the levels vary from one another (theme wise), and they are very detailed. I would say that the level designer and everything who worked on the artwork deserve an A++.But the game is essentially a walking simulator. All you can is really admire the surroundings. The controls i didn't like very much. First of all, you definately must use a controller. The controls are left stick and trigger for one brother, right stick and trigger for the second one. The problem is that whenever you want to use something, you have to hold the trigger. So, say when you are climbing, you have to hold down the trigger (else you will let go and fall). Thing is, in this game, it requires you to hold the trigger way too much throughout the 2 hours, so you really start feeling frustrated.The game is neither a good movie, or a game. I am sorry, but it's overhyped."
