76561198024315047,Recommended,225080,30741485,Posted: 25 March,all,Bill the Galactic Hero,"I bought it on sale for $3.39. Definitely worth it. I went through it slowly and I lost a lot of time when I had to restart a chapter due to a glitch. There is probably only really about 4 hours of gameplay. Still, I think I'd have felt satisfied if I had paid full price.The mechanic of playing two characters simultaneously is something new and fun. The puzzles are never too hard and you're not likely to require a walkthrough. It's really pretty. It manages to create a real sense of attachement to the characters as they go through so much to try to save their father.Be warned, however, that it is VERY linear. It is not a wide-open world for you to explore, it is a story for you to play through but there is really one way to play this game. If you can't enjoy that, even with great visuals and storytelling, buy another game.Spoiler Do not read this if you intend to play the game No, really, really don't. It's for people like me, who have finished the game:When big brother dies and you have to use the controller to controll just little brother for the first time since the beginning of the the game, it's really emotionally affecting. Suddenly playing with just one character now seems as odd as playing with two did at the beginning. That emptiness of somebody who should be there and who isn't is the closest I have ever felt to having a loved one die that didn't actually involve having a loved one die (yes, speaking from experience). Not for everyone, I guess, but a game that does something I've never seen before and made me feel something I didn't think a game could."
