76561198038389661,Recommended,225080,29333890,Posted: 18 January,all,choppy the panda,"Bravo, just bravo. This is the first time I ever write a comment on steam. I just have to say, very well designed game. And to all that´s considering buying it, just do it, it´s a small game with a big impact. And do use a controller to play this game, you can play it with keyboard but it won´t have the same meaning as a controller.In the beginning, the controling seperately the two brothers with 2 thumbstick on controller was a bit frustrating, but if you have played it, you´d understand what a monumentally impressing design that is for expressing the emotion of the game. Through the whole game, you are telling yourself, left stick is big brother, right stick is little brother, to the point that the controller has intergrated into the storytelling. And in the end when the big brother was incapacitated, you suddenly felt that emptiness on your left hand, and the urge to rush up to the tree and save him. Then you found out he´s already gone, the reassurence of the temporary disabled left hand in your heart became permanent, you geniuenly felt that lost in a way of your own control. However that wasn´t the end of it, the final part when the little brother refuse to step into the water and you can´t seem to find a way to make him do so made me emotionally angry. ""Your brother died for this, you gotta get over yourself little dude"" I was yelling inside. But no, he just refuse to go on into the water. After several minutes of trying, I was confused, angry, then suddenly I touched the left stick, the one representing the passed away big brother, and the little one moved, struggled through the water with his brother´s strength. I was all tearing up, controlling the little brother using the big brother´s power, pulling lever that was impossible for the little one before or climbing up the cliff too high for him before.... This game definitely deserve a medal."
