76561197994679910,Recommended,225080,8270801,"Posted: 25 December, 2013",all,zholobov,"The game surprised me multiple times along the way - even last seconds of final cutscene.Right from the beginning it surprises by its visual quality - it is very beautiful, by attention to detail - there are tons of details and tiny cute content you can miss by just running along the path, by its technical quality - very polished and almost flawless.Later it suprises by original and imaginative world and strange big and little details. And as you get closer to the end it gets more and more gruesome and morbid. Although first it seems like a fantasy game for children, especially due to casual gameplay and visual style, I'm not sure I can recommend a child play it.Gameplay-wise it is very casual and will not make you replay long sequences or test your hardcore gamer skills. But it's not mindless either. The balance is very precise to make it a game but not allow gameplay overshadow story or visual/audio beauty and immersiveness.I feel that creators were influenced by many classic games, and weave the influences very organically into the game. There is definitely strong influence from Ico in castle chapters. There is also very deep controller trick reminiscent of Metal Gear's one.Overall, this game seems perfect labor of love with no visible flaws. Except that in my opinion it's a mature game which can be easily mistaken for a child game, so the target audience will most probably not play it.Highly recommended."
