,Recommended,225080,34485199,Posted: 25 August,all,Space Nib,"I'll be honest here, I like this game but I feel like it is severely lacking in many aspects.The GoodAmazing atmosphere and tone, very eerie.Characters that work in synergy, interesting secondary characters.The game creates emotion and builds a stroyline without the help of words.Camera movement is extremely fluid and supple.The NeutralThe game is very linear and doesn't foster interest in exploration.Playing with a keyboard is possible but requires very good coordination.The quality of the graphics and character movements is no better than that of the PC game ofHarry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban, which is from 2004. I'm kind of willing to pardon it since this game is indie, but imho opting for a simpler art style would've allowed for more fluid animation and less clunky controls.The puzzles are very simple in essence, but many of them will be hard to solve because of the clunky gameplay.The game is very short. It took me 4 hours to beat it because I'm typically a slow player. Buy it on sale only.The BadThe reason why the controls are rather clunky is because you are expected to keep the spacebar and right CTRL buttons pressed down while moving around for long periods of time, which is very impractical and contributes to the fact that you need very good coordination to play with a keyboard.The controls are also buggy. At some points, when climbing walls and other obstacles, the character would randomly fall, as though the player had stopped pressing the spacebar/CTRL even though they didn't.The game has a bunch of bugs. It happened to me once that I was stuck at some point because a necessary cinematic sequence simply wouldn't trigger until I restarted my computer. Other users have reported bugs of similar nature.Long story short, it's a good game with solid ideas but it feels old and unrefined."
