,Recommended,225080,24061387,"Posted: 3 July, 2016",all,'b,"Positive:- Beautiful scenery (seriously, the character models might not be so impressive but the environment is stunning)- Nice music (a great atmosphere is created in conjunction with the scenery)- Fun and non-frustrating puzzles- Interesting controls- OK storyNegative:- Game is relatively short (perhaps 2-4 hours)- Controls can be tricky to get used to (especially if you're playing alone)- Not much of a challenge- Story is not as fantastic as other reviews seem to make it out to beConclusion:While the storyline is nice and tear-jerking, the scenery, music and game-play is what made this game for me. The world created for the Brothers is the major selling point! The story is OK at best, unfortunately. Not the most creative or mind blowing, but not mediocre either. Furthermore, the controls are creative but also confusing at the same time.When playing with a controller, you control each brother separately using the two analogue sticks and trigger buttons. Sounds simple enough, right? Yes, until you mistakenly let go of the wrong trigger button and one brother goes plummeting to his death. No biggie. However, I played this game twice: once alone and once with my girlfriend. When playing with a friend this becomes a much more enjoyable experience. Each player can take control of one brother by sharing a controller: one analogue stick and trigger button each. This basically nullifies control confusion. So grab your significant other and buckle down for a pleasant few hours!If you want to spend a few hours playing a very casual puzzle-platformer with great scenery then this is the game for you! Having said that, I wouldNOTpay full price for this game. Wait for a sweet deal and grab it then.If you enjoyed this review please follow me on mycurator page. Your time and support is greatly appreciated!"
,Recommended,225080,1547309,"Posted: 4 September, 2013",all,noibn,"I'll cut right to the chase on this one - this game is amazing. Seriously, like, really good. But if you're still on the fence, or want more details, read on...You play as two brothers, who you control at the same time using one controller (single player co-op, essentially). The left stick and left trigger button control the older brother's movement and all-purpose ""action"" ability, respectively, and the right stick and trigger similarly handle the younger brother's actions. For the first couple of minutes, controlling both characters simultaneously feels a bit awkward, but it quickly becomes second nature. The game does a nice job of easing you into the controls. Gameplay mainly consists of some basic platforming and solving puzzles using cooperation between the brothers. Brothers is not a challenging game whatsoever, and the path you take from start to finish is pretty much linear. On paper, those two things may seem like negatives. However, in conjunction with the rest of the experience, I felt the mechanics and ease of gameplay worked perfectly. This is not a game one plays for a challenge. It is a journey you take, experiencing the story of these brothers, in their quest to find a cure for their ailing father. This game is all about that journey, and experiencing the amazing sights and sounds of each new area and challenge that the brothers face. To add any significant amount of frustration to that experience would have been a huge disservice to the game. It feels just perfectly balanced exactly as it is. And that is all I am going to say (to get into any more specifics would defeat the purpose of experiencing it for yourself).Brothers can be completed in roughly 3-4 hours. Even though that's not a lot, I felt it was just about right. What you get out of this game is well worth every penny, even with the short length. This is, of course, assuming that you are into these sorts of low key, emotional game experiences. If that's not your cup of tea, you may want to skip it. But for anyone else, if you are at all open to these sorts of games, you absolutely must play this at some point (though I would recommend sooner than later, so as to avoid getting inadvertently spoiled).Technical notes: On the store page for this game, it states that a controller is required. While technically that isn't true (there are settings for keyboard in the launcher options), there IS a reason it says that. I really, really, REALLY do not recommend playing this without a controller. The wired Xbox360 controller works natively with no problem, but I would assume anything with two analog sticks and left/right triggers should be fine. The game was clearly designed around using a controller, and I just don't see how using a keyboard could possibly replicate that ""zen"" experience of becoming one with the controls well enough. But hey... do whatcha gotta do."
76561198065289104,Recommended,225080,19662638,"Posted: 12 December, 2015",all,Vanille,"Disclaimer: I have beat the game and have all of the achievements.This was an enjoyable game. The mechanics were interesting and something I haven't seen before. You control two brothers at the same time. They must work together to progress through the game. There is no English, or any known language for that matter, in this game. Surprisingly, this doesn't keep you from fully grasping the story. The brothers set out on a grand adventure, and you watch them grow emotionally, especially Little Brother.This game will give you the feels. It has a very touching story. Another surprise, the game had some pretty dark spots which I very much appreciated.I would highly suggest adding this to your wishlist and grabbing it on the next sale."
,Recommended,225080,16038403,"Posted: 28 May, 2015",all,Bouma,"A very charming game, I highly recommend this one to everybody. It requires a controller to play but that is half the fun. The left side of the controller is for the older brother while the right side is the younger brother. This makes the puzzle solving a bit more interesting in that a few times I found myself mixing up the buttons resulting in one brothers unfortunate death.This game has a lot to offer though even in the limited 3-4 hours it takes to complete the game with all the achievements. The story and characters are extremely likable and recognizable even though the language they use is completely imaginary. The art really got me too, there are these benches you can sit down in to observe the surroundings in a wide view; and I often hesitated to move on in the levels just to spend a few minutes taking in the scenery.People of all ages will enjoy this game, so check it out if you ever get the chance."
