,Recommended,225080,9782479,"Posted: 10 April, 2014",all,woodiland,"Brothers - A Tale of Two Sons---ABOUT---In this Indie-Action-Adventure we follow the story oftwo brothers, whom recently lost their mother ina tragic accident. And now they are faced with a newalarming situation, their father is ill and will soon die.The two brothers sets out on a adventure to recovera magic three juice that will save their father.---REVIEW---To start of, this is one of the prettiest indie gamesI have ever played. The graphics and art design isreally outstanding, and I found myself stopping upfor a brief period of time to just look at thescenery. Some of the scenery just left me in awe,it's a really unique world and the graphical stylefrom the landscape to the creatures in this gameis really wonderful.The world in this game is truly stunning.The audio is also getting a huge thumbs up from me.A huge variety of fantastic sound effects and asoundtrack which really fits inn with the situationsyou encounter in this game and the world we'retaking part of.The gameplay is special, creative and fun. I will note tho,that a game controller IS required to play this game, and Iwill explain why. In this game you control both of the twobrothers at the same time, the way they did this was dedicatingone of the two analog sticks to each of the brothers and oneshoulder button to each of the brothers. With the left analog stickand shoulder button you control the eldest brother, and with theright analog stick and shoulder button you control the youngest.This is a really fun and creative way to do this, and often bringsorientation difficulty during some situations. When the two brotherscross over to the opposite side of the screen from each other,the control sheme stays the same, so the controls in a waybecomes inverted. It's a fun challenge and I found myselfduring some situations just stopping up to get my orientation stright.The game combines this special control aspect of the game withsome intriguing puzzles, which will require some multitasking.None of the puzzles is especially hard to do, but they were funand creative. Tho because the game developers went for the choiseof giving this world an imaginary language, and not speciallymuch written text at all, there were a few situations I was lostas of what I was supposed to do, but not for long.As for the story in this game, it's really good. You'll get immersedin this world and continue adventuring to try finding a cure foryour dying father. You'll encounter some really dark situations inthis game, dark emotional situations, some of the situationsyou encounter might get to you and make you just think overwhat just happened. It's not a tale of happy rainbows and chocolate,it's a mature journey which will bring up subjects like death, suicideand the strong bond between two brothers.I spent approximately 3.1 hours completing this game, so it's notespecially long, and because this game really doesn'tbring much replay-value into it, I find the price tag of 14€ tobe a tiny bit too much, to be honest. But, this is an exceptionallybeautiful and mature tale of two brothers, in one of the prettiestgame worlds I've seen, so the 14€'s was worth it.---SCORE---I will pull some points off from ""Value"", because of short game timeand little to none replay-value.Graphics: 9.5/10Audio: 9.0/10Gameplay: 9.0/10Story: 9.0/10Value: 7.0/10Score: 8.7/10"
