76561198011233147,Recommended,225080,7918974,"Posted: 4 December, 2013",all,J3ST3R,"This must be one of the most visually pleasing and emotionally touching games I have played in recent years. Top that with some very creative controls (though at times confusing) and clever platforming and puzzles and you have the recipe for this game. The only drawback to be found here is the length of the gameplay, which must be considered quite short. But what it lacks in quantity it more than makes up for in quality. It is developed by none other than Starbreeze Studios, the company who brought us games like The Chronicles of Riddick, The Darkness and most recently Payday 2. So it is safe to say that they have had some moderate success already with proven creativity. It is clear to see the Scandinavian influences in this game in the way of backdrop scenery and folklore, and even the folky chants playing in the background.The key feature in the gameplay is controlling the two Brothers at the same time to solve puzzles. Therefore it is highly recommended to use a XBOX controller while playing this. That was also the intention of the developers, seeing it was first released on XBOX Live. I haven't tried playing it on the keyboard, but I feel that would be a bit awkward. Even on the controller it can be awkward at times, especially when the character you control with the left stick is on the right and vice versa. Something just crashes in the brain when that happens.It seems to me that this might be the start of something good. There is a lot of uncovered ground here both in the gameplay idea and in the world it is set in, and hopefully Starbreeze will build on this and release an even bigger title in the future. Short or not, I do not think you can play through this game without being awed in one way or another. Definitely recommend this to anyone who loves games in general and love new experiences within their favored media. Starbreeze certainly deserves your money for making an impact on the gaming scene.I rate this game a solid 9/10!Happy gaming"
