,Recommended,225080,29935752,Posted: 14 February,all,cheshire.panther,"Putting an emotional part and a story aside, this is essentially a old-schoold adventure game where you are playing two characters both at the same time on their quest of finding a medicine for their ill mother. The game uses gamepad in a clever way to let you do a hell lot of complicated moves using a tight-packed control scheme and the whole gameplay is based around it. There is a good dose of exploration, a good dose of scenary porn and a lot of small puzzle solving, where some of the puzzles are based on the physics engine and some require a bit of clever thinking.The game is relatively simple and not really stressfull, and I would say it is a bit cute in a way Undertale was cute or old school adventure games like LBA were.What I like about the Borther is how pixel-perfect it is. It's like a good movie - the perfect length, the perfect directing, a perfect pacing. There is nothing that you wish to add and nothing that you wish to remove.It's a great adventure of surpisingly long length, which never makes you tired,  ends at the perfect time and leaves a bittersweet and satisfactory aftertaste that keeps you remembering it from time to time and smiling."
