,Recommended,225080,14816635,"Posted: 9 March, 2015",all,𝔹𝕌ℝ𝔾𝕐,"AUDIOSoothingVISUALBeautifulDIFFICULTYChild's PlayVIBEMelancholyCRAVINGJourneyON SALEConstantPROS:There is a good chance you will finish this game in one sitting. It is easy to get invested very quickly. Gameplay is incredibly creative, and battle is not solely evasion tactics like you'd expect. Each level presents a new challenge, so there is no repetitiveness. You would think it would be hard to control two characters at once, but within minutes it was second nature. The story is told with no words, making it powerfully-poignant.CONS:It is almost nauseating how desperate the game is to tug at your heartstrings. If forced emotional investment through kicked puppies and weeping, legless orphans irritates you, don't bother installing; The gamestarts on a low note, and ends on a low note.It's got great artistic value, but that may make it a real drag. It is also very short, if you are purchasing for elapsed gameplay time, you will want to wait for this to go on sale. (My hours were racked up through completionist play.)WORTH:Brothers goes on sale all the time at a whopping 90% off! Wishlist it and wait for a sale to get it for $1.50 USD!OVERALL:I certainly believe that games can be art, but I've often questioned whether or not art can be a game. Brothers proves that there are successful marriages between the two worlds that don't land you in the ""walking simulator"" zone. It is reminiscent to the works of Team ICO, which I feel is a fitting description and the highest compliment I can pay a game.SCORE:10/10Full Review Coming Soon"
