,Recommended,225080,8181348,"Posted: 21 December, 2013",all,GothShinobi,"What a wonderful game!A story telling the journey two brothers undertake to find a cure for their seriously ill father. You control both brothers simultaneously, having to help each other to overcome the many obsticles they encounter.The puzzles can tax your co-ordination, as you try and maneuver the brothers into position and interacting with the correct one - but don't let this deter you; this game is telling you their story and the puzzles are just there to give you the sense of the struggles they come across.The sounds in the game are simplistic, but they work perfectly to set the atmosphere - the game doesn't even need dialogue, the actions of the characters and the random noises they make say all that needs saying to let you understand what is going on and what you need to do.The graphics in the game are beautiful. The art-style I would say is in the same vein as Fable, which again suits it just right, and will leave you wide-eyed at the various environments the brothers must progress through on their journey.The game may be short, but it is an experience you need in gaming. I highly recommend this!"
,Recommended,225080,13786087,"Posted: 2 January, 2015",all,Shyguy,"This is probably my favorite game of all time. It is a relatively short game, but the pacing of the game means you are encouraged to explore and interact with your surroundings (necessary if you want to get all of the achievements). The storyline is compelling, taking full advantage of the whimsical world you play through. The characters speak a made up language which I personally feel only enhances the experience as it means you're forced to pay attention to what the characters are doing, how they interact with others, and the tone of their voices. The game takes you through a series of environmental puzzles which are generally rather simplistic in solution, but the control mechanisms are challenging enough to keep it interesting. As soon as you've mastered the controls in one area you move on to another puzzle which introduces new mechanics.This game is an emotional journey- you encounter situations which bring the player in touch with feelings such as playfulness, fear, jealousy, joy, and grief.  I personally think that by making the controls so challenging and making them operate in such a way that you really have to pay attention to what you're doing, it makes the storyline all the more powerful and the ending that much more poignant. You don't always realize what you have and how much you rely on it until it is gone, and this game captures that experience beautifully.Basically, brace yourself for some major feels."
