,Recommended,225080,20164974,"Posted: 31 December, 2015",all,Tip Rex,"Amazing, one-session titleThis game is simply amazing. It seems like nothing great at first glance and I was unsure before buying it, but it was worth it. By worth it I mean the 1.49€ I payed, I don't think I'd recommend buying it for the full price.""Brothers"" is a very short game and I'd recommend playing it in one long session because the story really sucks you into the environment and it also takes a bit to get used to the unique gameplay mechanics. It took me just about 3h to finish the game, but I derped two or three times. If I knew what to do at every little bit I would have been able to do it in 2.5h.The StoryIt's really not a special setting. Having to complete a far dangerous journey to save a relative is nothing new. But the way it's done is just mind-boggling! The emotions I felt for these characters living through lows and highs (especially the highs are normally rare and hard to implement in sad games!) of their lives really don't compare to anything I have felt in a video game before.The only thing that isn't great about the story is that it is very linear. But that's okay.Rating 9.5/10Graphics & technical stuffThe graphics are really nothing special. The boys look kind of cute (not in that way! ;D) but the textures are boring. But that's not really the main focus of the game so that's okay.The physics do bug out rather often to the point where it get's a little annoying. For instance right at the start you have to push a cart with both brothers. To pick up the handles of the cart you will have to stand at very specific places with the brothers otherwise it doesn't work. They also move rather jittery sometimes.Rating 6/10Summary:Overall a definite recommendation, if it is on sale. It's a title you really only play once (linear story) and  that will really only take up one session. But for 1.49€ It's really worth it. Like a really good movie, just a little more involving."
