,Recommended,225080,9227657,"Posted: 22 February, 2014",all,joe,"It was famously said that ""[y]ou'd be hard pressed to find 10 games better [than Brothers] this year"" and it was lauded by some as the best game they’ve ever played but I went into Brothers: A Tale of Two Sons with a fair dose of scepticism.What started as a confusing system of solo cooperative play turned into a master class of environmental storytelling as I followed the titular brothers’ quest to find a cure for their stricken father. The journey that started in a quintessential village quickly gave way to the fantastical; each new area tells a story of its own through its presentation and together they are woven into the lore of this new world to explore.Not approaching the game as a puzzle or adventure game greatly enhances the experience. It felt more akin to an 3 hour epic. While it has some minor issues that I can’t mention without spoiling the game, I enjoyed the game overall and would highly recommend it. The last 30 minutes is when the magic happens.PS: play with a gamepad"
