,Recommended,225080,22501999,"Posted: 18 April, 2016",all,Boxa,"Brothers is a pretty good game, really well made. This game has a pretty unique and interesting mechanic, where you control both brothers. It can be a bit hard to master, but it is actually not unfair at all. Usually the game gives you pretty good time before hand, so you know what to do.It is better played with a controller, since you control each brother with half of the controller, but is actually playable with the keyboard. By the way, there is a certain part of the game that I couldn't pass with the controller, only with the keyboard, because of a bug, I guess.This game, unfortunately, has some bugs and glitches that can spoil the fun a bit. I even had to start a level again, because the mechanism of the level simply didn't want to work. But, it is still pretty short, so you won't spend that much time.It is also pretty, really pretty, and I mean it both aesthetically and story-wise. The graphics are actually simple, but it works pretty well and makes things really cool to admire.The story is actually pretty deep. Even though you don't understand a single word from the boys (they speak in a foreign language) their actions make for everything. Pretty well told.You will have some good time with it.Also, it is, at sales, at some pretty cheap prices."
76561198036574574,Recommended,225080,24199107,"Posted: 8 July, 2016",all,potatocat,"I don't speak Swedish, but without understanding a word, Brothers left me with lingering emotions long after I completed the game. Brothers is mechanically simple - the puzzles aren't very difficult and there aren't any complex gimmicks. The story is straightforward and progresses at an easy pace. The primary reason for playing this game is the story anyway. It's more than just the plot, I think, that made the largest impact on me and made it stick. The little details peppered throughout the levels tell stories on their own (i.e. complete the achievements!). The landscapes are utterly gorgeous (reminds me of The Lord of the Rings, actually), and vivid as well.It's a game worth playing but don't expect to just casually burn through it like any other - this is one to savor for the details and the storytelling. Highly recommended."
