,Recommended,225080,10821342,"Posted: 25 June, 2014",all,Jolly Roger,"TIME: 3 - 4 hoursDIFFICULTY: Low - IntermediateCONTROLLER: RequiredRECOMMENDED: YesA wonderful fairy tale; it hit all the right notes for me from whimsical to surprisingly dark. Visually it feels like it draws from Fable TLC with a touch of Shadow of the Colossus. I'm not a huge fan of the music by itself, but in the context of the game world, I think it does a great job at setting the mood of different set pieces.This game does have a learning curve, mechanically - both brothers are controlled simulaneously using the R/L sticks and triggers, which can get a little confusing. The gameplay itself isn't anything revelatory, but that ""dual control"" mechanic provides some interesting coordination puzzle opportunities.The only downsides were some technical shortcomings: choppy framerate that occasionally dropped to +/- 20 (but was stable at 30 enough to keep me satisfied) and texture popping can sort of take you out of it. I paid $3 for this on sale, but I think it's worth the full asking price of $15, even as a shorter experience."
