,Recommended,225080,8413447,"Posted: 29 December, 2013",all,MadCast: Bobgar the Warbarian!!,"The good:*  The gameplay is innovative.  Controlling both characters is neat.*  The puzzles are fun, if a bit simple.*  The world is fantastic and exciting.  Beautiful art and interesting setting.*  For the most part I was on the edge of my seat waiting to see what would happen on the next part of their adventure.The bad:*  The main storyline is aweful.  Extremely cliche, and where the designer expects the player to feel emotional impact there is none, because he never bothered to develop the characters in a meaningful way.  The last 15 minutes of the game were painful to paly through because of how forced it felt.  Luckily through most of the game the main story stays out of the way.*  The controls are cludgy when they work, and I had to edit a .ini file burried in the games configs in order for it to use my controller correctly (the left sticks Y was flipped, and the game's built in menus don't have ways to change things like that)*  The game is very slow to start (and slow to end)  The first 15 minutes of the game feel like pointlessly running around a town.*  The game is very short.  All of it high quality but it wont last you very long.Despite my gripes I found the game to be a lot of fun to play, and well worth the price of admission if you can pick it up on sale.  Just don't expect a deep story, and be willing to deal with some wonky controls.8/10"
76561198026703244,Recommended,225080,7607943,"Posted: 8 November, 2013",all,SnowRaven,"This is pretty much the most incredible game I've ever played, period. It simply cannot be recommended enough. I'm actually writing a recommendation for it immediately after finishing it, because it's just that good.The controls are amazing and fun, and they're often incredibly well used. There's no ""Press E to Perform Complex Action"" here. For example, you actually have to rotate the analog sticks to have your brothers spin a crank. The game's not completely unchallenging, but most of the focus is on overcoming and executing it rather than the usual annoying, long, drawn-out search for a solution to figure out the puzzle.The story is just absolutely wonderous, and without comparison to anything I've ever played in a game, or encountered pretty much anywhere, ever. It's fun, funny, and heartwarming at times; thrilling at others; and at points staggeringly sorrowful. I spent the entire end of the game crying, and I'm about to start again. This is also the first and probably only time I've ever found myself crying over a game mechanic, - it was just that amazingly touching. (You'll see what I mean at the end, I refuse to be more specific for fear of spoiling it.)This is the only time I've regretted buying a game on sale - I honestly wish I'd bought it for full price, just in the hopes of making it that much more likely I'd see another game even close to this good."
