,Recommended,225080,29465436,Posted: 24 January,all,Scabard,"This is a rather unique game. There is no dialogue really, everything is in another language. The story is told through actions such as pointing, showing objects, nodding etc. The characters and locations are well designed and give a genuine fantasy setting which oozes history and lore. But this isn't really where the game excells, it's the control method and puzzles that shine the most. You control both characters in the story with individual controller sticks and triggers. It can get a little confusing, especially if the characters move across the screen and you get confused about which stick controls which character. That said, the puzzles require you to move each character quite precisely at times, rotating objects held at each end by the two brothers or pushing a lever one way whilst pulling it another. The puzzles aren't hard, they aren't really there to tax the mind but when combined with the control method, it can provide a fun little challenge of timing and precision. The game is a couple of hours long but it's very high quality. Perhaps wait for a sale if you want your money's worth in terms of time spent but if you're looking for a good story and neat little challenge, this is worth the asking price.Some gameplay:https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pbDpLTj9jCM"
