76561198009430218,Recommended,225080,9864860,"Posted: 18 April, 2014",all,JacoRay,"A masterpiece; that's what Brothers: A Tale of Two Sons is.It's emotionally gripping with the storytelling as you watch the two brothers bond while adventuring to find healing water for their ill father. Straight from the beginning, you can tell that this isn't exactly a game suited for kids, as you watch your mother drown to her death in flashback cutscene, when the younger son, Naiee tragically tried to save her, but isn't able to do so in time. I don't wanna spoil anything, but the game is an adventure game that is charming, creepy and lastly, heartwrenching.The gameplay starts when Naiee and his elder brother Nyaa carry their father to a doctor, and from there the doctor has them embark on an epic quest to find the healing water. During the epic quest, you encounter folk in the village, farmers, sheep, rabbits, mountain goats; friendly trolls, evil trolls, whales, invisible monsters; giants that fought to their death, wolves, griffins, and much more.While you don't fight any of these beings, and really, only some of them are evil, (the mean trolls, a giant spider, wolves, and some angry cultists), you avoid them by controlling the two brothers. The game plays like a twin stick fighter or shooter, but as a 3rd person, over head view, and puzzle solving, one stick for each brother, and a trigger to interact with objects.The game really is epic with the interactions, as you climb, swim, swing, fly, use torches, use various gears and handles; there's a large number of puzzle/interacting; but it's pretty straightforward.The graphic style is reminiscent of Fable and Ico, but in its own way, and it works well as the game is gorgeous. The audio is perfect, the music and atmosphere really add to the charm of the game, as well as to the creepiness of certain areas (like the guy who tries to hang himself and you have to choice of stopping him, or the bloody rivers where the giants fought to their death, or the children whose bodies are hanging in the forests).I managed through the game pretty well, but I have to say that the ending is f*cking depressing. It leaves an emotional impact unlike any game I've ever played.10/10"
,Recommended,225080,25251459,"Posted: 30 August, 2016",all,Evaheist,"A gorgeous, deeply moving story set in a wonderfully rich fantasy world and very creative gameplay mechanics. This game is one of the best examples for video games telling a very touching story with many emotional grips and exciting twists and not sacrificing anything for accomplishing this goal.I couldn't recommend it enough.A wonderful and moving experience indeed. I loved every minute of it.SHOULD BE PLAYED WITH A CONTROLLER FOR THE IDEAL EXPERIENCE."
,Recommended,225080,11459622,"Posted: 28 July, 2014",all,viad,"Brothers: A Tale of Two Sons is an adventure/puzzle game with a unique control scheme, and an outstanding story that is one of the best around. This game is set in a somewhat fantasy world, boasting stunning vistas the brothers adventure forth in. The fantasy nature isn't as heavy as in games that make it a huge focus, since this game is more realistic in its graphical approach with well designed nature scenes. The fantasy elements pop up with some of the things the brothers interact with. Each of the characters are stylized with a less realistic style, but do stand out from the beautiful landscapes. As for the music, there are some instrumental and vocal tracks, but they are sparsely played throughout the game. They do put the mood when a song starts playing, and they do help emphasize some key parts of the story very well.What makes Brothers one of the most well recieved games is its story. This is one of the games you want to have no spoilers before playing. Two brothers, an older and younger brother, must recieve a special healing liquid from the Tree of Life to save their ill father. The story is driven in the game mainly by gestures and actions, as the people in Brothers speak in a fictional language.The other reason that Brothers is a great game is its unique gameplay. Players control both brothers at the same time in a kind of single player co-op game. Each brother can move around in all directions and have a context specific action button, making this game best played with an Xbox 360 controller or equivalent. The brothers mainly explore around and climb things. For some parts, both brothers have to work together in tandem or do specific tasks with each brother. The older brother is stronger and can pull levers and give a boost, while the younger brother can move between bars. The puzzle aspects of this game by using each brother in specific uses is great, along with the general idea of using two characters at once.This game is pretty short though, so expect the game to last about 3-4 hours. The difficulty isn't too hard as most puzzles can be self-explanitory, save for some parts that may be unclear as to what to do. The achievements take some exploring and thinking to complete, but they are optional side quests and not part of the main story.Brothers: A Tale of Two Sons has its strong story along with a unique control scheme. Well recieved by many to recieve various awards, this game will certainlly enthrall players with a good emotional story and an interesting adventure with puzzles controlling two brothers at once."
