76561198092587756,Recommended,225080,24262048,"Posted: 11 July, 2016",all,RollWave,"A tag that should be higher for this game is 'platformer'.  Fortunately, the game guides your character and does most balancing, jumping, etc for you so you don't have to worry about falling off ledges.  But there are quite a few instances of skill jumps.  They aren't particularly difficult, but aside from the minipuzzles of figuring out where to stand your characters to activate the next thing, it's the primary game element.I recommend this game, but it's a minor recommendation.  It's an easy platformer/puzzle game with a unique control scheme, controlling 2 characters at once.  Finished in about 5 hours.The scenes are cool looking.  There is an overarching storyline, but 90% of the game is ""here we are, in this room, how do we get out...oh there's a thing we can push/pull/lift/activate...click on that' cue cutscene leading the characters to the next room, ""ok, now how do we get out of here..."".I would not purchase at full price.  But on sale 80% off or something, sure go for it."
