,Recommended,225080,8404554,"Posted: 29 December, 2013",all,Erbkaiser,"Brothers uses a very interesting control mechanic, where either analog stick controls one of the two brothers. All levels are designed and take full advantage for this.But that's not why you should play this game.Brothers has no real speech throughout, and what music there is is perfectly matched to the levels. The art design is also beautiful, at times as if you're in a LOTR-kind world. You move through several environments here from villages to high mountains to a frozen world, yet all belong to the same world clearly and it is a wonderful journey. But that's not why you should play this game.So many games try to touch emotion and portray a feeling of loss, but few succeed as well as Brothers does. One of the most impressive games ever made. Play it."
