,Recommended,225080,8655321,"Posted: 10 January, 2014",all,AA,"I understand if you are reading these reviews as you are sceptical on whether to buy this game or not.  I was once like you.I originally witnessed this game release on Xbox LIVE Arcade on the Xbox 360 and soon after a media storm ensued - praise was given everywhere from nearly every major gaming outlet.  I still didn't bite.Roll around Steam Winter Sale 2013, I buy Brothers for £3.  Yep, £3.  Possibly the best £3 I have ever spent, on anything.To truly experience this game you will need a controller as this is a ""Single player co-op"" experience, you will be controlling the two brothers on the one controller - One brother using the Left analog stick and trigger and the other brother using the right hand side.  It is difficult to get used to, it is very unfamiliar, at times uncomfortable and it is absoloutley incredible. The way the controls are mapped and how they are used in gameplay tell a narrative that you are probably thinking is impossible, especially when the characters speak a kind of ""Simlish"" language.  Without spoiling anything, these controls are mapped in an EXTREMELY smart way - Please think, if you play this game, why each brother is mapped to that specific side of the controller. Hint: It was not done on accident.Brothers: A Tale of Two Sons takes so many conventions we have become used to in gaming and completely flips them on their head, and then some.  Take nearly everything you know/have learned about modern games and throw it away before heading in to this.The audio is great, the visuals are near perfection.  I can not say any more without spoiling this experience... Just buy and play this game, It will be like nothing you have ever experienced."
