,Not Recommended,225080,33058395,Posted: 30 June,all,Perdix,"TL;DR - A short, shallow game in which it is expected that the (not to be understated) novelty of the control-scheme is expected to carry the user's interest through an otherwise bland experience set in a beautiful environment.I can see why people liked it, but after being recommended it by plenty of other peeps - I don't think I'll pass on the recommendation.  I grew up playing games on PC and never had a console - so games like this that feel like classic PS1/PS2 games (but with updated graphics and a neat control scheme) don't have a nostalgia-itch to scratch for me; so I have to look at this game based on its other attributes :The Good---------------The art style and world-building are beautiful and very atmosphericThe sound design is gloriously richThe controls for this game were satisfying to use (note : I was using steam-controller)The Not-So-Good---------------If you're expecting a good story to immerse yourself into them oh boy keep looking. There's no story aspect in this game that was developed further than the back of a napkin.For a puzzle game, there's, like...no puzzles. You just keep moving forward and doing the immediately obvious thing and then the game ends.I can see why people would like this game, but after the first 30 minutes I was just bored; it was clear that there were no surprises or additional mechanics that would change things up.  It feels like a wasted opportunity in which a game clearly meant to tug at your heart-strings gave you absolutely no reason to care about anything that was happening.Not for me, it seems."
