,Recommended,225080,13735381,"Posted: 31 December, 2014",all,rss,"First of all - CONTROLLER IS NOT NEEDED, STRETCHED FINGERS ARE.Well, I must admit that I'm rarely able to finish any game in one go, but on the other hand, new games are getting shorter, this is why I prefer to avoid them.However -Brothers - A tale of Two Sonswas totally worth the price (normal or discount ones, really). It has everything a good tale should have - good, yet simple plot, brave and bad characters, amazing views and miracles happening, funny and sad moments, not to mention all the little secrets that were not resolved and are all up to you in interpretation.I truly enjoyed the gameplayand the idea of brothers cooperating in order to achieve their target. I was playing using a keyboard so you may imagine that it wasn't the best and most pleasuring way to experience a game, but I took it as an extra challenge. Some parts were quite hard, it takes some patience to master the characters jumping for example. I must admit I loved the gameplay - it feels like you are watching the movie, and I haven't got this feeling since playing Fahrenheit. Well, both are adventures but this isn't simple 'pick up and use' story. I have a feeling that this would break the wonderful atmosphere this game has.Music and graphics- My respect goes to authors of this game. For me, personally this is the best Eye candy game since a long time, it reminds me of Fable at times, but this is a different genre of game. Here it feels really.... surreal, Mythical landscapes meeting mythical characters creating simply wonderful atmosphere.Speaking of sound -you don't need to know englishor any other language in order to play this game. Brothers and all characters met by them are speaking the worldwide known, universal language known as the sign/body language. It becomes very clear what is their target, where they are going and what are they thinking at the moment.You shouldtry this gameif you are a true fan of adventures. Sure, it can be hard at times but wasn't Fahrenheit the same when it came to controlling the keys and pressing them frantically? If you want to spend a nice evening and have wonderful dreams try this game. And this comes from a guy who rarely plays new adventure games.9/10 - Will play again to discover all hidden places and achievements.+ Graphics and the Music, the Atmosphere, Holy♥♥♥♥♥♥ rainbows and aurora Polaris.+ Funny mini bosses. The idea of characters cooperating (Playing them at the same time) makes the game challenging and not as easy at it may seem.+ Characters language. Oh, Becuase everyone in the fairly-tale-like world should know English, right?+ The world. The mystic lore of the world, leaving you wondering what exactly is going on. I want to visit it again!+ Some ideas for puzzles were pretty nice.- Should be longer! Really, I wouldn't mind seeing 2-3 stories, each with 6 chapters. Or some special modes.And eh, for most of the game I couldn't help but think how the hell they are going to make their way home. Eh, Could be worse."
