76561198013874018,Recommended,225080,8498493,"Posted: 1 January, 2014",all,Staplehead,"Brothers - A Tale of Two Sons is simply put, one of the best game I have ever played. Never have I been so captivated by characters whos words are mere emotional cues.You are dropped into a world which has a delightful charm on its own and control two main protagonists in which you solve puzzels and explore the fantasy world that Starbreeze has created. You are taken on an adventure with epic proportions with some helpful (and evil) characters who can help guide you and create a great tone for the game. One thing that I really found interesting about the game is that even though its charm gives off a somewhat  happy tone for the game, however Starbreeze has shown in this game that no matter how the game looks you can also give off a very grim mood as well and I am glad that they chose to create a somewhat mature story that people can understand and possibly relate to the characters. The Starbreeze developers we're able to create a world with great visuals and also had a very simple goal in mind but allowed you to choose for yourself what really happened story wise by not giving the characters much oral interaction. Even though there isn't oral interaction between the characters (that we can understand), you can easily tell what emotions the characters are feeling and I think it was a fantastic feature.I hope you enjoy this game as much a I did. I also hope that you forgive me that I left out a lot of information about the story because I would like you to experience it on your own and my input would most likely affect how you feel about the outcome.~Ratings~-Visuals 10/10--Sound 9/10- Could have seen maybe more ambient sounds at some points-Gameplay 9/10- Great puzzles however some trouble sometimes haveing the characters activate some keyparts in the puzzle or characters getting stuck (VERY RARELY)-Replayability 7/10- I would say if you beat this once you will most likely not pla