76561198038271086,Recommended,225080,8829108,"Posted: 24 January, 2014",all,brylv426,"This is the perfect game for an adult gamer.What I mean by that is the gamer who's got a job, family, other responsibilities and thus wants a gaming experience that's tightly focused, with no wasted grind-y nonsense. A gamer willing to understand that a ""good"" ending and a ""happy"" ending rarely converge.Brothers is a deceptively simple game that is, in a word, beautiful. Think of the first twenty minutes of Wall-E or the first ten minutes of Up: a simple, wordless parable told in images and movement with not a single wasted gesture.This is a game that respects its audience tremendously and, in turn, earns that respect back.I offer a single caution: set aside three hours and play the entire game in a single sitting. I made the mistake of playing it for a few minutes each day over the course of a week and I thin, unfortunately, that blunted the impact of the experience for me."
