,Recommended,225080,8588322,"Posted: 6 January, 2014",all,mleako,"I gotta say that all those great reviews kinda ruined the game for me because my expectations where very high. If you want to play it purchase the game with ""I heard it's all right, i should give it a try"" attitude and you will not be disappointed.Now to the game itself. It's simply beautiful and touching. Graphics are minimalistic and simple but the designers managed to create astounding sceneries spiced with norse tales and mythology. The gameplay brings a new element where you control both brothers at the same time with different analog sticks on your gamepad (in my case on keyboard since I didn't manage to make my trust gamepad work in this game, not even with x360ce) and one interaction button for each character. Then you have to use both brothers to solve simple yet clever puzzles like climbing a rock tied to each other using swinging to reach otherwise unreachable areas. The game is not hard in any way but that is not what it is aiming for.The main aim is to deliver a touching story about two brothers who lost their mother and in fear of losing their father as well they set up on a dangerous journey to find a cure for their sick father. First it feels like a fairy tale when you meet a troll who lost his wife and is trying to help you but later on it turns into more like a horror atmosphere.To sum up this game is great yet I had slightly bigger expectations since everyone has been calling it the game of the year. The only negative I found is that the game is pretty short. It took me 3 and a half hours to complete and when it ended I was hoping for some more material which didn't come. Well but since I bought it on sale for 4,12 euros I don't give a damn. Buy it because this is a one of a kind game even though it could be longer and imo it has a lot of dormant potential."
,Recommended,225080,7682655,"Posted: 17 November, 2013",all,YardGnomeNinja,"If you have the smallest shred of a heart you will appreciate the beauty of this game. The art, sound and storytelling are astounding. The lack of voice-over, apart from the minimalist Germanic-gibberish, perfectly evokes the characters' personalities and feelings.Then you get to the gameplay. This is a game where simply watching gives you only 3/4 of the story. The controls, especially when using a 360 or PS3 (with motioninjoy) controller, provide a sense of closeness to the characters and at times give meaning to the situation.You control each brother independently with the analog sticks and interact with the world for each with the left and right triggers. Those are the controls. Contextually, each brother will react to the current situation and positioning (which is extremely forgiving).I finished the game in one sitting. It took me about two to two and a half hours. Do not let this deter you from this wonderful experience. I didn't spend as much time in the world my frist playthrough as I intend to the next.I simply cannot recommend this game enough. It is easily the most powerfully moving game I have ever played."
