,Recommended,225080,8666902,"Posted: 11 January, 2014",all,Avibhrama,"Borthers A Tale of Two Sons is providing us a unique gaming experience. It is adventure platforming game with coop gameplay that you control the big brother with your left analog (or WASD if you use keyboard) and right analog for the little brother (directional buttons in keyboard). You will control both of the character at the same time to cooperatively solve the puzzle throughout the gameYour father is dying sick, and your mother has died prior of the game. You, the two brothers, begin the quest to find the magical ancient tree that believed to have the cure of the disease. And the adventure begin. You will journey the beautiful world that's so believable. Every detail in this game is really well made, imaginative and even your adventure is short, you will still find something surprising in your journey. The story itself, it's simple, really simple that you won't struggle to understand what's going on. But not predictable and will arouse your emotion. Even they speak in ""not an actual language"" like how The Sims character speak and the animation is not like L.A. Noire that motion capture the expressios of the actors, you will still able to feel the emotion of the character, amazed by how the thing turned out. Playing this game is like you read very good pop up fairy tale books but with the story development that is not like usual fairy taleThe gameplay is simple, just movement, rotate the camera, and interact but can be quite entertaining. You need to do a combination of the older and little brother to solve the puzzle and do the platformer in this game. The elder brother is bigger and stronger, capable to handle heavier task like pick up a sheep or pull the heavy lever. And the little brother is smaller and lighter, so he can pass the fence or being boosted by his big brother to reach a high platform. Each character has it's role and the cooperative combination of them make an solid puzzle solving adventure. The puzzle itself is simple and relatively easy to solve but not boring, entertaining and unique in every encounter you will face. Don't expect to see a same puzzle in a different place in this game. Every stage has it's own unique puzzle and platformingBut this game has zero replayability, except you want to look achievements that you may overlooked in the previous playthrough. But despite of that, there are no reason to play it in the second time. And people who seek for challenge in their gaming experience will be dissapointed in this game. This game is very easy and not gave me a hard time at all. And off course the game is really short. Four hours to finish it including some exploring or interacting with some of the NPC'sMy score is 8 out of 10. The game is short, really short but so enjoyable. Fear not, with a cheap price tag this game is worth your money. If you like some simple and emotional story with unique and easy gameplay but can be very entertaining. This game is maybe for you. If you are someone who want a challenging puzzle platformer or someone who want more complicated story telling, I don't recommend you to play this game"
