,Recommended,225080,14377975,"Posted: 7 February, 2015",all,Sibarraz,"From a longtime, I had  heard good things about Brothers - A Tale of Two Sons.  The main selling point was the amazing story that the game had.Without seeing any trailers or screenshots, I bought the game, this was cool since I didn't know what kind of game was in front of me, so everything was new to me while playing the game.In a brief summary, Brothers is Adventure game where you had to guide 2 brothers in their quest to retrieve a medicine to heal their dying father. The first thing that I had to say is that this game could be a little frustrating at times, since you had to control the 2 brothers at the same time, for this reason a dual stick controller is required since you had to use them to move both brothers separetely, so you will need some good coordination at times. Also If you separate them too much, they will not move until they get closer, so this could be a drag.The main mechanic of this game is to solve puzzles and do some plataforming. This puzzles are SUPER easy to he point that it will be almost impossible for you to take more than 3 hours to beat the game on your first playtrough. The only challenge in this game could be the coordination required to solve some puzzles, but after a while that will not be a problem.With those 2 points in consideration, one could said that this game is average at best, so, why is so well regarded? Well, for everything else.The narrative in this game is very good, without shouting a tangible word in the whole game,  you could understand the whole point of the game through good animations and storytelling. The easy puzzles start to get a point since they help you to tell the story, and also to enjoy it without getting stressed. The atmosphere of the world and the music is also top notch, helping with the narrative in a way that isn't very common in this genre.And also, the most important thing in the game, the ending, which is so powerful that you could never forget it, and that once you can see it, you will  want to start the game again to analyze the whole game in retrospective, and start to appreciate way more the narrative of the game, even in some moments that could seem very trivial at the beginning of he game. The second playtrough is more relaxed since the game is shorter when you know what to doSo in resume, if you want a challenging game, Brothers isn't for you, if you want to play and interactive movie with great graphics and music, buy it."
,Recommended,225080,13438669,"Posted: 18 December, 2014",all,Sereni-tea,"This is simply one of the most beautiful, charming and touching games I have ever played. The graphics and artwork is beautiful, the characters are beautiful, the soundtrack is beautiful and the story is beautiful. I know I just used the word 'beautriful' four times in the same sentence, but it really is the best word to describe this game.Though the game isn't very long or difficult, the gameplay is unique in that you control both brothers at the same time with the same controller (or keyboard, though I imagine that would be a tad more difficult) - one thumbstick for each. The puzzles themselves aren't terribly hard, but having to control both brothers (often doing two different things) adds a nice bit of spice.The story, well, I don't want to spoil anything, but basically two brothers must go on a journey to find a cure for their dying father, who I affectionately called Jorgen. It may sound simple, but it is really much deeper than that, and explores issues like coming of age, love, trust and death. It does so in a refined, elegant manner, avoiding stereotypes. Perhaps the only thing I could have wished forwas a happier ending, though I do understand and appreciate why it had to be the way it was. I really didn't want the Big Brother to die :(Also, if you are looking for an easy game to get 100% achievements in, this game is ideal. None of the achievements are hard, and are more like rewards for exploring everywhere and interacting with everything. You can get them all in one playthrough if you like, or if you miss any, you can just load up the individual chapters without having to replay the whole game.I highly recommend playing this game, even if you only play it once. It will touch your heart and you won't be able to forget it for a long time."
