,Recommended,225080,2581664,"Posted: 25 September, 2013",all,wahtzy,"I better start off with this: I was recommended to play this by TotalBiscuit, as I had seen his 'WTF is' before I played the game. He said that this game might be the best game ever made in his opinion, and I started the game with that in mind.Now, as to whether or not this is the best game ever made, I will let that be up to you, but I can say that I don't think it's the best game ever made.It was a really nice movie.Yea thats pretty much my opinion  There isn't a whole lot of actual gameplay in the game, it is mostly running from point A to B, get up this cliff, get over this bridge. And the gameplay that was there, could be a bit confusing, because you had to control two characters at once. It was pretty easy to get past, and the times I got confused wasn't really enough to pull me out off the game.I think this game could be defined as a story driven puzzle game, although the puzzles wasn't all that hard, and more often than not, they were very simple. I didn't really encounter a puzzle that really had me think, and all of them was pretty much obvious. The gameplay of this title is in my opinion the weakest part of this game, and it is pretty weak. If the story and world hadn't been there I would say it was a pretty bad game.Speaking of the world. I got sort of a Zeno Clash vibe from the world, because it had the same way of having wierd animals, trolls, and oversized buildings lying around. It had sort of the same psychedelic dream setting, although not anyway near as weird as Zeno Clash. I really liked the setting, and the game uses a system with some benches that function as vistas as you sit on them, to show off the world.The world definitely had a lot of wackiness to it, and the chapters where sort of themed, as you pass through the different areas.The graphics wasn't anything good, and it was obvious to see that the game is optimised for xbox (although I have heard it shouldn't run all that well on xbox). Textures weren't all that high quality, but that didn't really matter as the art style is a cartoonish style. Although it came for xbox first, the pc port, if it even is a port, is pretty good. I had a steady 60 fps all the way through, and not a single lag spike.As for the controls I personally played with a controller, which seems to work the best as well  but I tried the keyboard controls and they seem to play just fine, so really don't HAVE to play with an xbox controller but it is recommended.I saved the best for last: the story.The story is definitely the strongest part of the game. The story is really good, and Starbreeze somehow managed to convey the whole thing without a single real word. All spoken language in the game is pretty much gibberish (it might be a real language, but you aren't expected to understand anything from it). Even though everything said is gibberish, it is really easy to understand the messages conveyed between the characters of the game. And there is absolutely no problems in understanding the story.The story is very emotional, but it didn't make me cry, as it did TB (guess people really are different after all ;)). Although single manly tear at the ending.So is this worth buying. In a way, you can think of as this: it is pretty much the price you would pay to go see a new movie in the theaters  so if you are looking for a great story, in a game Wahtzy could beat in 2 hours 33 minutes, this would be worth it. If you are looking for an actual game, I would say this isn't worth the full price, and if you aren't interested in story at all I would say you should pretty much just avoid it. As for replayability, I only managed to get a single achievement, so I guess there is a reason to play through it a second time.TL;DR:If you are looking for a movie length game with a great story then BUY IT.If you are looking for a game to play, secondarily with a good story, then: Buy it when its on sale.If you are looking a game, but aren't interested in story at all: AVOID.Edit: I corrected a lot of spelling errors. Turns out I can't spell opinion."
