,Recommended,225080,8722556,"Posted: 15 January, 2014",all,SpaceHarrier,"""Brothers"" is the kind of game you can sit down and play through in a few short hours - but it's a complete package with an interestingly fresh control scheme, a moving soundtrack, and a story that was surprisingly moving - especially for a game with no actual dialogue. A gamepad controller is needed to play, and each of the two playable brothers are assigned to one of the gamepad's control sticks, with the trigger on either side assigned to that brother as a general ""interact"" button. Though it may take a bit of getting used to, the controls end up tying into the story by the end in a way that really took me by surprise. If you've got a free afternoon and are a fan of adventure and story, this game is definitely worth a play."
