,Recommended,225080,8387868,"Posted: 28 December, 2013",all,DomoKnight,"What the game lacks in length, it makes up for in depth.  Brothers is a unique experience that is reminiscent of the games put out by Team ICO.  You're dropped into a world with only the most basic of instructions:  travel to a far away place to get a cure.  The controls took a little getting used to since you're constantly controlling two characters at the same time, but after about the first chapter or so, I was surprised at how natural the dual joysticks worked for this game.  The scenery is gorgeous and the puzzles are fun (if not a little on the simple side).  My favorite chapter is the one where you're traversing the corpses of fallen giants.  No explanation is given or needed as to why there are newly fallen giants all over the place; in fact, each level has its own charm of unexplained circumstances.  Nevertheless, the level design is superb and the mysteries of the chapters do not detract whatsoever from the experience.  My only complaint is that the game is relatively short."
