76561198042276382,Recommended,225080,14850438,"Posted: 12 March, 2015",all,Emile,"Brothers is something special. I do not believe any review could do judgement to the sheer creativity this game has. Two brothers have to save their father and embark on a journey to find some magical medicine from a tree. While the premise may not sound most interesting, its simplicity combined with the extremely clever narrative create gamings first true artistic classic that will likely be credited as an inspiration for many generations to come.One can see from the screenshot that the world is gorgeous and epic. When actually playing it this breathtaking feeling keeps recurring, and the game offers more than enough moments to truely take the environment in. The gorgeous music also adds to this.The characters itself, while speaking gibberish, are animated with great attention to body language and tone of voice, to make it really easy to identify with them. They come across some very interesting scenarios, and the differences between the two brothers are made clear using the aforementioned techniques.Instead of stripping a lot of gameplay to tell a story like many other narrative focused games, Brothers manages to offer well-designed challenges that synchronise very well with the narrative itself. At no point does one feel like there is a divide between the narrative and what you do in the gameplay, like in many, many other games.I could go on for hours, as there is no game that got me thinking as much about gaming as a whole as Brothers. The ending is by miles the most memorable event any game has offered me, and it still lingers to me to this day.I'm feeling a strong 10."
