,Recommended,225080,18408990,"Posted: 10 October, 2015",all,Daniel Murphy,"Absolutely amazing. Easily one of the greatest experiences I've ever had with a game. I don't think a game has ever evoked so many personal emotions from me. I am a younger brother and my elder is 6 years apart from me. This game truly touches me on a deep level with the utilization of sound, music, lighting, voicing, expression, and atmosphere.Although the characters speak in an indistiguishable language (mostly, apart from the brothers' names), their vocubulary leaves nothing to be desired and is communicated flawlessly. I believe this was intentional and means to give the player the ability to fill in the blanks with what (s)he feels appropriate, which is likely something personal and easy to connect with.The characters themselves are easy to relate to and offer excellent development as characters. The story is extremely simple, but communicated in such a beautiful way, I can't help but be floored this game lasted me nearly 3 hours. I already want to play it through a second time and find if there was anything I missed (other than achievements which are very satisfying and well hidden) which would give more richness to the world itself.The character models may not suit my taste, however, the art style makes up for any personal issue I have with the models themselves. I've taken a handful of screenshots from this game and am one right-click away from setting one as my desktop background.The game itself offers many puzzles and challenges which are never frustrating, yet still require thought and patience to accomplish. The flow of the gameplay has never once been interrupted for me and leaves very very little room for criticism. I'm greatly impressed with how the developers managed to keep such a simple mechanic of using two joysticks to control each brother sp fresh and entertaining even while repeating some puzzles over again. The game continually gets easier as the player becomes accustomed to the mechanics, but there are plenty of instances where I've had to stop and rearrange the brothers because I had trouble keeping the two moving naturally. This is not the game's fault at all, rather it is my own and the game should be praised for continuing to challenge me with such a simple and logical mechanic, but still retaining its challenge by requiring constant attention. Excellent puzzles and mechanics; they offer many challenges.I highly reccomend this game to anyone who enjoys puzzles, challenging multitasking, rich worlds with deep story, has an appreciation for music and environment, and especially anyone with a brother (hell, even a sister) who they care deeply for. You will not regret this purchase or the time you invest into it."
