,Recommended,225080,16882479,"Posted: 4 July, 2015",all,ShmuPixel,"An excellent game, but way too short and no replay value... I cannot recommend buying this game at full price knowing those two facts. On the bright side though, the storyline is somewhat disturbing (in a good way) and the puzzles won't blow your brain out. It's more like an exploration game with a few platforms/levers/NPCs to interact with. You get into the game very quickly and enjoy the journey, but it doesn't last and you get that weird aftertaste of a game that is too short and too easy. Definitely a game for a casual moment if you don't know what else to do. It took me 2.5 hours to finish and I could have spent maybe 30 minutes to an hour if I wanted to unlock all achievements, but there is not really any incentive to do that. I'm not 100% sure if I should recommend this game, even though I really enjoyed the 2 hours of gameplay. I don't think it's worth its price so I'm going to conclude with ""only buy it during sales or in a bundle"". It's still a good game that you should definitely try."
