,Recommended,225080,10259993,"Posted: 27 May, 2014",all,nick.,"Despite the actual game being pretty short, ""Brothers - A Tale of Two Sons"" is a simply-put emotive adventure alongside it's beautiful visuals.=STORY=Shortly after their mother's death, the two brothers' (Naiee and Naia) father has non-specifically fallen ill. After they bring him to the village's doctor, it is revealed to them that the only way to cure their father is by collecting water from the ""Tree of Life"". And right then and there, the brothers begin to embark on a long journey (and dangerous at times) to save the only parent that they have left.=GAMEPLAY=You are in control of the two brothers: Naiee (young) and Naia (eldest). Despite the fact that this game requires the Xbox 360 controller for the better experience, I used the PC keyboard personally. To be honest, it was a bit iffy to get used to, but then it wasn't such a big deal for me. The brothers will interact with others that they come across on their journey, solve puzzles in order to advance, and do what brothers should always be doing: Working together.=VISUALS/ART=Visually speaking, I love it. Seeing the amazing areas around you while you're traveling to the Tree of Life is breathtaking, making you want to appreciate the outdoors much more with praise. There are also moments in the game where you can sit on a bench that are on the edges of various areas, high in elevation, showing the beautifully looking environment that surrounds you. Once again...breathtaking.=MUSIC=Musically speaking, it's great. I really adore the parts of the soundtrack that are so calm and peaceful to listen to, and the parts that make you feel like you are embarking on an amazing journey, much like the two brothers themselves=FINAL VERDICT=A simple, beautiful story that comes with amazing visuals and a really adventurous soundtrack certainly does make up for the short length of the game.On a scale of liver to chocolate, I give this game: A ""Nutella"" rating."
