76561198019927859,Recommended,225080,13875583,"Posted: 6 January, 2015",all,\m/-___-\m/ | Mr. G,"A beautiful game.  A Narnia-esque world accompanied by a musical score that accents all the emotional moments, as well as utilizing silence in some of the best ways I have seen in video games.  A modern twist on a side-scrolling platformer, 'Brothers' has you controlling two separate characters with each joystick (or opposite sides of the keyboard), and I recommend keeping each brother on the side of the screen that corresponds to his control side.  This control scheme works brilliantly and I am sure will be copied for years to come.All I will say about this game is that it is a must play.  The collision detection can be off, some pop-in may occur and your character might not do exactly what you want on occasion, but to let any of these minor flaws deter you from playing this game would be a shame.  It manages to bring together ideas from games like Uncharted, God of War, Journey and Heavy Rain all into a 3 hour storytelling masterpiece.Worth it at full price, easy, and the biggest steal ever when it goes on sale (80% off on occasion!). Do yourself a favor, buy this game.  Take your time.  Explore off the beaten path, when you can, and just enjoy it.  Do your best to avoid spoilers and you will be handsomely rewarded."
