,Recommended,225080,13828624,"Posted: 4 January, 2015",all,jagaricosalad,"Brothers is a game where two brothers embark on a quest to bring back water from a giant tree far away from home to cure their father. I didn't really expect anything when I bought and played this game, and boy I was in for a treat. The cinematography in this game is amazing, there are many times you would have that urge to just stop for a moment and take a screenshot of where you are.In this game, you have to rely on what you see to understand what is happening. The characters do speak, but you won't really understand much since they speak a fictional language. This does raise a few questions here and there, but overall they do a fantastic job at painting the tone of the world. The gameplay is unique, and I recommend using the controller for the best experience.Storywise? Amazing. There are several memorable moments, some of joy while others of somber and they sure know how to hit them feels. During my initial playthrough I had mixed feelings about the story. But upon rethinking I can appreciate how they did the story. This is a story of two brothers, travelling in a beautiful but harsh world. They live in a world where there is love and kindness, but they must also be cautious and prepared for the dangers hiding in every corner.The only thing I would complain is that the playtime is a bit short, but other than that it's a 10/10 to me. Highly recommended game."
