,Recommended,225080,13509149,"Posted: 21 December, 2014",all,Oasis,"A Tale of Two Sons proves you don't need blood, guts, gore, crashes, explosions, bullets, guns or nudity to make an AMAZING game. If you must have those things to enjoy a game choose a different title. This game has an engaging story albeit a little straight forward plot. The brothers must work together as a team to solve puzzles and accomplish tasks although none of the puzzles is overly complicated they are not necessarily straight forward either.The BEST part of this game is the awesome graphics and engaging storyline. You want these brothers to succeed in their task of finding the cure for their dad's ailment. You'll be drawn into each scene by the beauty that surrounds you. The details truly breathtaking. If you allow yourself to become emotionally engaged in the story you may even get chocked up near the climax of the story.Two improvements are (1) I wish there was more interaction between the two brothers after successfully completing a task or navigating a tough area ... i.e.  high fives, warm embrace or celebration. This would show just how much these two brothers love each other and make the climax of the story even more powerful. The second (2) improvement would be to have decisions made in the game effect different outcomes. Right now you either get a puzzle right or interaction right or you don't proceed ... Yes = move forward with story - No = do it again until you get it right.Overall I'd give this game a 9/10 for what it is ... a 3-4 hour visually & emotionally engaging puzzle solving story. Knowing what I know now I would DEFINITELY BUY THIS GAME again!Hope this review is helpful in your decision to buy this game. Go ahead ... you won't regret it as you don't need the elements of my first sentence to enjoy a gaming title."
