,Recommended,225080,13673256,"Posted: 28 December, 2014",all,JawZ,"I got this game for just over £1 in the sale and for that price is was absolutely worth it.It presents itself as a game that is very short and very sweet. I finished it in just under 4 hours with all the achievements. Asuming there is no sale, you will have to question whether you are willing to spend £11 on a very short game. The story and graphics are beautiful and the only other thing that has stuck me emotionally in a game is the Walking Dead. Prepare to pay for quality (in abundance) and not quantity.I loved every second of the game. The camera angle was always focused on the boys one way or another ; you knew what was happening at every second. It suprised me how such simple controls (1 stick big bro, 1 stick lil bro-1 trigger big bro, 1 trigger lil bro) could actually be used in a range of puzzles and multiple scenarios.There isn't too much in the scheme of negatives, but heres a few:-Missable achievements. I HATE them.-The game displays itself as a sort of puzzler. I found the 'thinking' part of the game far too easy and I never got stuck on anything (not to toot my own horn). The average person will not have to think much. It seems the game wants to show off visuals rather than give us puzzles.-In a few instances the boys interacting with some objects was glitched (not holding handles in the hand properly) but that is minor.-Too short (obviously)-You need a controller to play which is fine and works but you are limiting your market audience. Just introduce big bro as WASD and little bro as arrow keys with the mouse to turn the camera. Its suprising how many people don't have a controller.In conclusion-if you are looking for a lot of content and lots of replay value, spend your £10 on Borderlands 2 and put in 100s of hrs. If you looking for a memorable, mesmerising gaming experience with beautiful visuals and you have a controller then buy it and put in 3-5 hours. I VERY MUCH RECOMMEND you do not rush the game. Take every second in and experience at the game. I've finished and I don't intend to play it again for a long, long time because I know the story. I don't see why I would want to restart.While it is on sale for a few pounds, BUY IY!Come on people it's pocket change we're talking!"
