76561198170667375,Recommended,225080,13896799,"Posted: 8 January, 2015",all,Kai,"I played this game with an xbox controller so this is how I am reviewing it. It was really interesting and challenging to control both of the brothers at the same time. One half of the control controlled the younger brother and the other half controlled the older brother. The controls, however, weren't difficult to understand since only the 2 scroll buttons and the triggers are used.Past the controllers, there was absolutely no dialogue which kind of threw me off at first, but once I played a bit more, I realized the game didn't need dialogue. The story was pretty straight forward, however twisty it DOES get at the end, and it gives you exactly what you need as you go through it.The graphics and artwork in this game are absolutely astounding. I'd play this game over and over again just so I could get a look at the scenery. There are little benches all over so if you see them, PLEASE sit down and scroll around you really will not regret it, it's amazing.The story isn't very long, but it still makes you feel very attached to the characters. This is much more like a visual story game than anything, even though you control the brothers, because there is only one ending but the story is so interesting that it's worth it.I didn't really find anything I disliked about the game. I mean, yes, it was a bit difficult to control both of the brothers at the same time, but I think that added to the interest level. I feel like if I was only playing one of the brothers, it wouldn't have been so imersive. This also made me feel connected to the two brothers because I was able to see how most of the things you needed to do, came with the reliance of the two brothers. You wouldn't have been able to finish the story if you didn't have both of them..."
