,Recommended,225080,24016821,"Posted: 2 July, 2016",all,NightFall,"Although it is a pretty short game (took me around 3 hours including cut scenes), it was pretty entertaining. The game pretty much goes like this: you control two brothers (simultaniously) as they go on an adventure to cure their sick father.  This may be a difficult game for someone who can't do two things at once (since you control two characters at once), although if you have a friend play the game with you, it will probably be ridiculously easy. There are some awesome visuals throughout the game and although the gameplay is very simple, it does not get boring and it isn't too easy. There are several ""puzzles"" which aren't too difficult and even a few that don't have to be completed to finish the game that add little cool things to the story.The one thing that really caught me off guard with this game is that it gets pretty dark and gory as the game goes on. I was kind of expecting a child-friendly game, which it does give off that sort of atmosphere, but then it starts throwing in lots of blood and disturbing things (rivers of blood, guy trying to hang himself, etc.).Overall, it was a fun, somewhat challenging game with really great visuals and very good (and emotional) story.I'd definitely recommend this (especially if you catch it on sale), unless you were expecting this to be a kid's game. Definitely not for kids......."
,Recommended,225080,24015770,"Posted: 2 July, 2016",all,VengeancE #Yin,"First of all, ""do not try to play this on a keyboard"".Go for keyboard only if you have a keyboard with anti-ghosting or n-key rollover since multiple keys are to be pressed at the same time.Now coming to the review.This game is marvelous. There were a few cons (At least for me) but the pros outweighed them and the story most of all, pretty emotional and great.Gameplay was fair, controller definitly helps but on a keyboard, its pretty hard to play it since you control both charecters at the same time.Coming to the pros :-1) Marvelous story2) Pretty emotional3) Good world interactions4) Epic scenery5) Spots to view that sceneryCons :-1) Camera angle is literally not good most of the time even after setting it through the 2 keys (Which only allow you to move it left and right without any height adjustment. Height adjustments are prebuilt and cannot be altered).2) Even though scenery was good, camera angle was not good enough most of the time. Also not enough sitting places to sit and watch the scenery.3) Probably it is me (Could be my GPU issue)  but the game appears in 4:3 ratio most of the time. I would have preferred widescreen but as i said, it could be an issue on my part.A pretty good game overall. Should you buy it ? Yes definitly. Should you buy it at full price ? NO !. Should you buy it in discounts, Hell yea.Coming to the story, story has pretty good elements, pretty normal story however, there is something in this story not there in others.This story does not hit you when you think it is supposed to hit your feels (Many people have said it i guess), however, it will hit you at a place and when it does, you will be having teary rivers running through your face (Happened with me).Game does not have an actual language (or even if it has, i dont think most of us will understand which language is that), but no need to worry, game is designed that way. You will understand each thing perfectly so do not worry about this.Spoilers below, see at your own risk :-It does not hit youWhen older brother dies.It hits you (as in my case)When their father visits the grave and then thinks all this is cause of him and cries."
76561198000756087,Recommended,225080,24116207,"Posted: 5 July, 2016",all,Tom,"By far the best story-telling in a game I have ever experienced. The game mechanics are simple but innovative, with the player using only 6 buttons to control both characters and the camera. At first controlling both brothers feels unusual, but by the end of the game it's second nature.A variety of landscapes are presented with incredible beauty. It's a game that will certainly provoke your emotions, with moments that are both heart-warming and heart-wrenching. It's this balance between joy and tragedy that makes the story so compelling.For a game without any intelligable dialogue, the story is told effectively thorugh more subtle means. Without revealing any spoilers, the ending of the game in particular finds a way to present an incredible depth of character development given the short length of the game, and does so directly through the game's control system. This is one of the many highlights of a very artistic and unique game, and I can't think of any other game where the player feels such an emotional connection with the story simply by pressing a button on the controller.I don't think I've ever cried playing a game before. This game however, was an exception..."
