,Recommended,225080,8635754,"Posted: 9 January, 2014",all,Wolfie,"Feeling. Something that is the sign of an amazingly written story. It is also something that alot of games lack in recent times. There are plenty of fun, action packed triple A games out there, and a nice selection of story oriented RPGs, and the indie game market has been booming. But 'Brothers: A Tale of Two Sons' has something very unique about it. There isnt a word of english in this short little story, but it's controlls are extremely simplistic, yet unique in their own way. You control two characters simulaneously with both analogue sticks. The game itself is very short, but it has one hell of a sound track, and a suprisingly emotionally empacting story considering there is not a word of english to be found in th game. You start the game and think 'This is a little odd, and slow, not sure if I like it really.' Well, that's the though process I had at the time anyway, but giving the game a chance, I soon found myself becoming immersed in the beautiful world of 'Brothers'. And I played it in one sitting until finish. And was very suprised at how much I ended up loving the game. It's really something that you must experience yourself to fully understand the appeal, but I do highly reccomend playing this game at some point in your life!"
