,Recommended,225080,19561544,"Posted: 7 December, 2015",all,Crackers,"Please read the notice that a controller is REQUIRED to play.A moving game that is simple to play and takes you on an adventure both visually and emotionally. Only gripe is the control scheme which does take about 2-3 minutes to understand but from there the game is a pleasure and a treasure to play. It does not take long to complete (hence why many reviewers only have about 3 hours on record playing it). This game is more about telling the story of the game as the player solves puzzles or accomplishes objectives within. A few camera pan issues and some small deterrents exist as the control scheme and some puzzle mechanics take a second to understand. This would affect a game critic's scoring but the game is solidly put together and designed.Although short, and will be an easy game to get all the achievements in, I found this game to be well worth the price of admission. This game is not a must buy mainly due to the factor of ""replayability"" but I do recommend playing it.If ever found at a discount in a sale, and if the price of admission for a few hours of gameplay sound good for an evening then I would recommend this game. If you like games with puzzles similar to earlier games like ICO, Shadow of the Collossus, and early Tomb Raider - just not as in-depth, then this is the game for you.For everyone else, although I do recommend this game, it does not scream to be bought, it kindly asks for your time and leaves you with a good ""feels trip"" where you are greatful for having given it a chance."
