,Recommended,225080,23992894,"Posted: 1 July, 2016",all,buster3mc,"This game messed me up. 10/10It was a short but beautiful story about two brothers finding medicine for their sick dad. I called the young men Righty and Lefty. There were a wide variety of strong atmospheres, and they could change unexpectedly. The graphics were phenominal. Rather than focusing on realism, the developers wove a beautiful story through the whimsical aesthetic. Somehow the same song, which played during key moments, was able to take on so many different moods. It could be glorious or sorrowful, but it never changed. The use of the control scheme to further the story and feed the player emotions was extremely well done. Its a great game, and anyone with a gamepad should buy it, especially on sale.Also, the game itself is amazing. Even if you severely dislike story-based games, don't worry. The developers didn't sacrifice good gameplay for storytelling. I didn't expect this game to be difficult, but it had a nice challenge, and I found it very fun.tl;drThis game may be short, but it has perfect graphics, music, and gameplay, and anyone with a gamepad should be ashamed to not have it."
