76561198024730969,Recommended,225080,24191692,"Posted: 8 July, 2016",all,Jaydos,"Brothers - A Tale of Two SonsTL;DR One of those gorgeous games that feels like you're ""playing a movie"". Gorgeous visuals, music, sound and animations all combine with an engaging storyline to deliver an experience that won't be forgotten any time soon!Things you should know before purchasingLocal co-op and single player only.Game is actually completely playable with a keyboard. I controlled both brothers with my keyboard and didn't have any issues at all. Using a controller will make the game's controls feel much more intuitive however.Single player is A LOT harder than co-op. Be prepared to get your left and right hands very confused :p Still very playable though, if you have no friends or your brother is a jerk (like mine) :'(The puzzles are pretty basic. This game is very much storyline driven, so for the avid puzzle-solving gamers out there, don't get your hopes up on that front.The game's settings are as minimal as it gets. You get an option to change the game's brightness (gamma), the game's music volume and sound volume. That's all.There's no option to spoon your little brother (or curl up into your big brother's arms) beside the campfire at night... :')Very little replayability value, but given how good the storyline is, the price of the game and most importantly the type of game that Brothers is; this can be easily forgiven.What you can expect from the gameCompleting the main storyline~4 hours but I took a bit longer.Completeing all Achievementsan extra ~4-6 hours if you start a new file and explore every nook and cranny.Trying to force the two brothers to cuddle up to each other in front of a gypsy giant~7 minutes.OverallThis game is an absolute delight to play. I would however not recommend buying this game for the full price unless you're the type of person who cries non stop at the end of an emotional anime/TV series. This tale of twosonsbrothers will definitely stick with you for a long time, however it is hard to justify paying $15 US for a game that offers about 6 hours of gameplay.Get this game on sale and you'll have a wonderful new gem added to your library.Peace!"
