,Recommended,225080,18593832,"Posted: 20 October, 2015",all,Maximus,"DISCLAIMER: This is my first ever review. Please forgive me if my spelling or grammar is incorrect.Let me start by saying that this is not a 10 hour game experience.This game is roughly 2 to 3 hours of playtime.It is a story of two brothers who make a long journey, trying to find a cure for their sick father.It is mostly a casual game trying to pass some very deep meanings and emotions in way that sets it aside from the norm (breaks many cliches).I am not gonna spoil anything. I'm just saying that if you are willing to give this one a try, have a pair of tissues in close proximity.I am not going to grade any of the aspects of the game, because I believe that numerical grading is a flawed way of sharing your experience. Instead, I am going to put my experience into words as best as I can.The graphics are very stylish and, along with an excelent sound design keep the the ambience of the game constant and fluid. The soundtrack is also top notch and well executed.The controls are as simple as they get (not much to say here), though they are not the core of the game. Rather, they are a guide for helping you experience the feeling and tension of the game.The story( which is the meat of the game) is  simple yet deep and compeling. Almost like reading a very good short novel. You want to finish it in one go (which is what I did)All in all, I find Brothers: A tale of two sons to be an excelent game. I haven't regretted a single euro of my purchasing of this game, even though it's a short one."
