,Recommended,225080,20441208,"Posted: 9 January, 2016",all,Lamanai,"Game Name: Brothers - A Tale of Two SonsOriginal Release: 2013Personal Rating: AEstimated Playtime: 3 hoursMultiplayer/Coop?: NonePlayed on: Steam ControllerBrothers- A Tale of Two Sons is a great game. I received my Steam Controller a while ago and decided that I needed to get into the groove of using a controller. I've always used a keyboard and mouse combo, and this seemed like a great game to use the controller with, and I couldn't cheat and use KB/M since it is controller only.Controls:  The controls are very simple to use. A joystick to move and the trigger allow the brother to use their special move. The twist? You have to control both brothers at the same time. On the steam controller this meant using the joystick and the right touchpad. Was it useable? Definitely. Not to mention that it was easy enough for a controller noob like me to get used to.Graphics: The graphics are very indie-ish. This isn't a demanding game at all, but what makes it special is how the graphics interact with the artwork and the background to create the story. The creators place benches around the game and through the brother's special moves, you are able to sit down and observe the scenery.Music: The music fits the mood perfectly. From the funny and entertaining interactions that the brothers have with the other characters, to the scary and odd moments that leave you satisfied with the way that the scenes end.Overall: Highly recommended. It is basically an interactive movie. The cut scenes meld together with storyline, audio, art and graphics that allow you to forget that you are playing a game. You will love entering the world of brothers trying to save their single father, all the while speaking an unknown language, and will have you crying by the end."
