,Recommended,225080,14165188,"Posted: 25 January, 2015",all,Miri,"I started Brothers - A Tale of Two Sons with no expectations in particular and woah was I blown away. Despite it being a fairly short game (about 3 hours) it was a very memorable and unique experience. The story is a simple one: you play as two brothers going on a journey to find medicine for their sick father. Their adventure takes them exploring through Scandinavian style landscapes, through forests, caves and snowy lands, and you will meet creatures and animals of all sorts, both friendly and not so friendly. The emotion and atmosphere in the game is superb.You can play with both keyboard and game controller, I played using the latter one. In the gameplay itself you take control of both brothers at once using the joysticks and right and left trigger buttons (to interact), and the game has made good use of these mechanics for puzzle- and task solving. It may take some time getting used to, but the learning curve is fair and in most cases you know what you must to do to make progress.If I were to pick on anything it would be the non-real language they speak. In the beginning it put me off a bit and made some moments seem almost unintentionally comical, but as I played I got used to it. In hindsight I admire that they have conveyed the story of the game so well without a ""real"" language, and maybe because of it more people can relate to it.Brothers - A Tale of Two Sons is an amazing game and it kept me excited all the way to the end. If you enjoyed Journey on PS3 you will enjoy this."
