76561198058978274,Recommended,225080,27467999,"Posted: 25 November, 2016",all,TurboTurd,"In Brothers - A Tale of Two Sons you follow two siblings Ayi and Nayi on a quest to find a rare plant to save their dying father. The game features an interesting way to control both brothers: left joystick and the left shoulder button control the older brother, and right joystick and the right shoulder button control the younger brother, which are both controlled simultaneously to navigate through the game world and solve puzzles. Without any (understandable) words mentioned to the player, the game signals quest items through clever camera movement and interactions between the brothers. The game takes a comfortable 3-4 hours to complete and is very enjoyable for winding-down after playing a more stressful game.Overall, the game is very enjoyable and worth its price. The art is beautiful, the music is amazing, the sound effects are well-done and the story is easy to follow.TIP: If you regularly mix up both character controls, try to keep the older brother (Nayi) on the left of the younger brother (Ayi), since Nayi is controller with the left hand and Ayi is controlled with the right hand."
