,Recommended,225080,24432678,"Posted: 20 July, 2016",all,sir chap el victorious,"The best game i have played to date and the first one i would consider perfect (aside for one small bug).If you enjoy games like Journey, i recommend you play this. Don't look at any spoilers, just make a few hours of spare time and play through in one session.Note: Please use a controller! Took ages of messing with and old gamepad and JoyToKey for me BUT ITS WORTH IT!This is gaming storytelling at it's best. Pure hart and soul was put into this game and it shows. The pacing of the game is excellent, the enviorments enchanting. This game is avalible in every language there is, yet there is no text or perceivable dialogue. The game features movie like storytelling. There is so many small details that constantly made me smile. Written by movie director Josef Fares the feel of the game is amazing.This is the kind of experience you would get from a movie. It a nice (depressing) 3-4 hour journey . There is no real choices to be made, you are just along for the ride. But it really doesn't matter since the ride is superb.The gameplay machanics are fun and integrated into the story better than any other game i have played. Nothing feels tacked on or gimmicky, everything serves a purpouse in the story. The puzzles are smart and refreshing, not incredebly hard (which is good) but interesting and never repetitive.I feel there is so much unused potential in term of videogame storytelling. It is games like Brothers that tap into that potential. And it is with these kinds of games i feel this medium truly shines and offers something diffrent to other plattforms.Sure i will not play this game of thousands of hours, but unlike my most played games i can actually take away something , like a great book or movie. This game has deep meaning behind it.Ultimately this game is elegantly crafted and more than worth the asking price. Especially if you compare it to ♥♥♥♥♥♥ 120€ AAA games with 172 DLC packs and micro transactions."
