,Recommended,225080,11158397,"Posted: 9 July, 2014",all,Amr0,"I picked this up in the Steam Summer Sale, thinking nothing of it really. Just another game going cheap to add to my collection. No hurry to install, just leave it there on my list until I'm bored one day.....Well, one day I was bored, so I installed it and, with not much expectation I loaded it up. Well, to put it simply.......What a game! You start with two brothers, whom, after a short series of events, find themselves embarking on a quest to save their father from an unknown illness. The story itself is something of a rarity, something truly compelling. Despite being short, I found myself utterly involved with it and couldn't put my controller down. As the quest reaches it's conclusion, you will find yourself shocked, amazed and somewhat shaken. You won't forget this one in a hurry.Graphically, the game is beautiful. Stunning vistas will come and go, with weather effects that are equally as good. Character animations are brilliant, and really help to enhance the emotional impact and carry the storyline (these characters don't speak English, the game uses it's own made-up language). I lost count of how many screenshots I took, the game looks that good!Sound wise, the soundtrack is excellent. The music is full of ambience and really gives the game an extra lift. Characters and environments also sound really good.In terms of gameplay, the game is unique. I would highly recommend a controller to play it. The left stick is then used to control big brother, and the right control for little brother. This is still quite a challenge but, much much easier than trying to use a keyboard, trust me. Some of the puzzles and climbs require a little finesse, I died a few times trying to get both brothers across a few of the jumps and up some of the climbs, but overall, it works well.In conclusion, a highly recommended game that's well worth your time and the rewards it has won. 9/10"
